<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. suff. 30. The suffect consul of 30 must have been a senator before 31. He was probably a son of the senator of 63 (MRR 2.496). Appian mentions a Balbinus, one of the proscribed, who returned after the pact of Misenum in 39 and later became consul; his attitude at the time of the conspiracy of Lepidus in 30, as told by Appian (BC 4.50), justifies identifying him with the suffect consul. See above, on the senator named in the SC de Aphrodisiensibus in 39, L. (Attius? or Lucilius? or Saenius?) L. f. Ouf. Balbus (Syme, CPh 50, 1955, 133; J. M. Reynolds, Aphrodisias and Rome 57, Document no. 8, 68-69; see also E. Wistrand, Horace's Ninth Epode 15-16).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7151 .
